gw.api.webservice.maintenanceTools

Class ProcessStatus

  • java.lang.Object
    • gw.api.webservice.maintenanceTools.ProcessStatus
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ProcessIDStatus, GWRemotable, java.io.Serializable

    public class ProcessStatus
extends java.lang.Object
implements GWRemotable, java.io.Serializable, ProcessIDStatus
    Contains information about the status of a previously started batch process. This could contain status information for a process that is currently running or for a process that ran was run in the past. If the process is not currently running, the opsCompleted and failedOps fields won't have any useful information.

    • Constructor Detail

      • ProcessStatus

        ProcessStatus(java.lang.String type,
             java.util.Date startDate,
             java.util.Date dateCompleted,
             java.lang.Boolean success,
             java.lang.Integer opsCompleted,
             java.lang.Integer failedOps,
             java.lang.String failureReason,
             boolean running)
        Note: The process is running if dateCompleted is null
        Parameters:
        type - the type of process
        startDate - the date that the process started running
        dateCompleted - the date the process finished, if it has in fact finished
        success - whether or not the operation completed successfully, or null if it hasn't finished.
        opsCompleted - the number of operations the process completed
        failedOps - the number of failed operations
        failureReason - if the process failed to complete, the reason why it failed
        running - if the process is still running. Note that the process may be finished with all its work, but is still running, performing post-processing cleanup.
